               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Lat_liturg_f_31-item1" n="1" class="#liturgica">
						               <title type="desc" key="work_10507">Book of Hours</title>
                     
                     <note>
                        Hours of St. Margaret, with nine lessons at Matins; starting
                        imperfect in the invitatory psalm (at Ps.94:3, at '||nus super omnes does
                        ...') due to the loss of a leaf before fol. 1; ending imperfect in Ps.118:30
                        (at '...elegi iudicia [catchword:] tua ||'); the first three lessons at
                        Matins are I. 'Dum per uniuersum orbem per sancti spiritus alumpnos ...',
                        II. Tempore illo quidam prefectus nomine olibrius ...', III. 'Altera uero
                        die stipatis quam pluribus militum cuneis ...'.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                    
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>
                     <secFol>
                        <locus>(fol.1)</locus>nus super</secFol>
                     <secFol>
                        <locus>(fol. 2r)</locus>tempteruerunt me</secFol>
                  </p>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="perg">
                        <support>parchment</support>
                        <extent>i (paper) + 71 + i (paper) leaves.<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>130</height>
                              <width>90</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>80</height>
